I6. Notes on the applicability of the multiverse ensemble hypothesis

    - inapplicable
        - unlike the cosmos’s fine-tuning for life
            - which the multiverse ensemble hypothesis might suffice to explain
                ∵ the effect there, our creation and short-term survival, is already attained
        - the {cosmos’s support} for long-term survival cannot so be tucked away
        - but sticks out as surprising, inexplicable by that hypothesis
            ∵ the effect here, our long-term survival, is yet unattained
